go sit with the wallflowers.

522
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,999
I'm not used to leading.

523
00:43:53,880 --> 00:43:56,110
Come on, give the girl a glide.

524
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:59,192
No. I think your little brother
prefers to dance alone.

525
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:04,234
No, thanks.

526
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:09,550
I never touch French cigarettes.

527
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:30,799
Your brother's a good dancer.

528
00:44:31,520 --> 00:44:32,919
Big heartbreaker.

529
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:35,992
A couple of turns, that was it.

530
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:37,549
Really?

531
00:44:38,160 --> 00:44:39,639
Got them right in the knees.

532
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:42,389
Practically had to
carry the girls off the floor.

533
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:44,435
Really?

534
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:48,231
Have another drink, Frank.

535
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:49,949
No, I'm sleepy.

536
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:51,798
Go to sleep then.

537
00:44:55,960 --> 00:44:56,949
Alright.

538
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:15,556
I think I just lost my chaperone.

539
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:17,994
You're safe.

540
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,714
So where do you keep
your blue ribbons, Mr. Baker?

541
00:45:27,960 --> 00:45:29,279
Frank keeps them.

542
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:41,359
Nice night, huh?

543
00:45:48,680 --> 00:45:50,193
It's quiet, it's like...

544
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:53,390
the whole world is asleep.

545
00:45:58,440 --> 00:45:59,509
Careful.

546
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:03,317
I had too much to drink.

547
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:06,476
Champagne goes right to my head.

548
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,955
- Maybe we should call it a night.
- Yeah.

549
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:39,994
Miss Diamond!

550
00:46:44,920 --> 00:46:46,035
These just arrived for you.

551
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:48,712
Looks like you have an admirer.

552
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:51,435
There's no card.

553
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:54,269
The gentleman said
he would be in contact with you.

554
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:58,558
He's with the cat food convention.
I can have put them in water.

555
00:46:58,720 --> 00:46:59,835
No, that's alright.

556
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:13,155
It's nice.

557
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:16,509
It's nice.

558
00:48:27,800 --> 00:48:31,793
It's been 5 years since
I've seen you without a cigarette.

559
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:34,634
The whole room upstairs
smells like an ashtray.

560
00:48:34,880 --> 00:48:36,871
You know that? The sheets,

561
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:41,395
the carpets, the drapes.
The towels, my tux, my shirt.

562
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:44,078
Want to smell my shirt?

563
00:48:44,280 --> 00:48:45,474
Maybe later.

564
00:48:45,920 --> 00:48:49,276
I'm not kidding. Do you know
what an insidious habit that is?

565
00:48:49,440 --> 00:48:53,433
How many do you smoke a day?
Must be hundreds!

566
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:59,591
This is just a wild stab,
but is something bothering you?

567
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:03,234
Leave her alone.

568
00:49:03,960 --> 00:49:05,154
I mean it.

569
00:49:05,760 --> 00:49:09,230
This isn't a hatcheck girl you can
leave behind at the Sheraton.

570
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:11,231
You've got two shows
a night with her.

571
00:49:14,280 --> 00:49:15,838
You don't know what you're saying.

572
00:49:16,160 --> 00:49:18,913
I know trouble,
and it's name starts with 'S'.

573
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:21,117
Do me a favor, Frank.
Relax.

574
00:49:21,360 --> 00:49:25,239
Do me a favor, little brother.
Stick to cocktail waitresses.

575
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:33,759
Meeting here each night,

576
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:36,229
sharing these few moments,

577
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:39,314
I feel as if we're becoming
one big happy family.

578
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:42,912
The fine wine, the music...

579
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,789
What's all this mean?
I don't know. Who's to say?

580
00:49:46,120 --> 00:49:47,519
All I can tell you is...

581
00:49:47,680 --> 00:49:50,274
it makes it very special
for us here...

582
00:49:50,560 --> 00:49:53,199
to have you out there.
Right, Susie?

583
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:54,429
Right, Frank.

584
00:49:54,800 --> 00:49:55,994
Right, Jack?

585
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:57,469
Right.

586
00:49:57,880 --> 00:50:00,519
But if I can add one more thing.

587
00:50:01,440 --> 00:50:02,793
I love you, Frank.

588
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:05,030
What?

589
00:50:07,200 --> 00:50:08,349
I love you.

590
00:50:09,880 --> 00:50:11,359
I just wanted to say it.

591
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:21,030
You came in late on
"Little Green Apples".

592
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:23,432
- Excuse me?
- You heard me.

593
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:27,030
No, Frank.
You came in early.

594
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:32,195
- You have for the past decade.
- I never missed a beat.

595
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:35,430
I never miss the beat!

596
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:37,318
That's because you make it up.

597
00:50:38,480 --> 00:50:39,595
Take it back.

598
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:41,713
Take it back?
What's this, the 3rd grade?

599
00:50:41,880 --> 00:50:43,074
Take it back!

600
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:45,558
Take a kiwi, Frank.

601
00:50:49,920 --> 00:50:52,354
Go to bed, Frank,
or this will get ugly.

602
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:55,397
- Yeah?
- Yeah, come on.

603
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:58,116
It's the fucking Newlywed Game.

604
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:00,635
- You hit me.
- I told you I was going to.

605
00:51:12,320 --> 00:51:14,117
Hello? Yeah.

606
00:51:16,800 --> 00:51:19,553
No, this is 512-B.

607
00:51:19,720 --> 00:51:21,915
Mr. Baker is in 512-A.

608
00:51:27,120 --> 00:51:28,269
Urgent.

609
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:30,916
No, never mind. I'll get him.

610
00:51:33,480 --> 00:51:34,833
We made a deal.

611
00:51:35,480 --> 00:51:37,516
Training wheels for a month,
then we would see.

612
00:51:37,680 --> 00:51:38,999
He ran into somebody's car?

613
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:42,516
Mrs. Ramadino's station wagon.

614
00:51:42,680 --> 00:51:44,159
It was parked on the street.

615
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:47,278
Got a pencil?
Pencil anybody?

616
00:51:48,720 --> 00:51:49,436
Here.

617
00:51:49,600 --> 00:51:52,273
I want you to take down
the New Year show.

618
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:55,116
10 o'clock you start with
"Thanks for the Memories".

619
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:57,589
- Then you segue into...
- "Happy Days Are Here Again".

620
00:51:57,760 --> 00:52:01,230
- I know the show.
- Then the song from Camelot.

621
00:52:05,480 --> 00:52:07,038
Don't hesitate to call.

622
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:08,555
Come on.

623
00:52:14,680 --> 00:52:16,318
Any word from Egghead?

624
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:21,839
I saved you the crossword.

625
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:26,189
Thanks.

626
00:52:42,680 --> 00:52:43,908
Well, happy reading.

627
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:19,829
Hear anything yet?

628
00:55:20,880 --> 00:55:21,915
Not a peep.

629
00:55:25,560 --> 00:55:27,357
I'm going to take a bath.

630
00:55:48,360 --> 00:55:50,749
Yeah?

631
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:52,755
It's Frank.

632
00:55:53,760 --> 00:55:54,988
So how's little Frank?

633
00:55:56,240 --> 00:55:58,196
Good. That's a relief.

634
00:56:00,120 --> 00:56:02,429
No, I understand.
Call me when you have time.

635
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:03,794
<i>What are you doing?</i>

636
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:06,714
We're taking a bath.

637
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:08,999
I mean...

638
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:12,639
Susie's taking a bath.
I'm doing the crossword puzzle.

639
00:56:13,400 --> 00:56:14,389
Okay.

640
00:56:14,760 --> 00:56:15,749
Bye.

641
00:56:17,920 --> 00:56:19,035
Kid's in the pink.

642
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:20,915
Good.

643
00:59:12,720 --> 00:59:15,678
<i>Boys and girls,</i>
<i>find a friend. This is it!</i>

644
00:59:15,840 --> 00:59:19,833
Ten, nine, eight, seven...

645
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:24,154
six, five, four, three...

646
00:59:24,680 --> 00:59:26,432
two, one...

647
01:00:21,880 --> 01:00:23,074
So...

648
01:00:24,320 --> 01:00:26,151
make any resolutions?

649
01:00:28,120 --> 01:00:29,394
No. You?

650
01:00:31,560 --> 01:00:34,279
No. I figure that stuff
is a bunch of crap anyway.

651
01:00:36,440 --> 01:00:38,749
- You do what you do, right?
- That's right.

652
01:00:41,320 --> 01:00:44,630
Old Egghead would've blown
a gasket seeing us here tonight!

653
01:00:50,520 --> 01:00:52,112
You're good, aren't you?

654
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:00,759
I can carry a tune.

655
01:01:02,520 --> 01:01:03,873
You're better than that.

656
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:14,232
I saw you guys once.

657
01:01:16,880 --> 01:01:18,359
You and Frank.

658
01:01:20,280 --> 01:01:21,554
At the Roosevelt.

659
01:01:23,320 --> 01:01:24,958
Must've been a cheap date.

660
01:01:28,480 --> 01:01:29,879
Soap convention.

661
01:01:30,320 --> 01:01:31,435
Soap?

662
01:01:32,680 --> 01:01:35,274
Yeah, they got
a convention for everything.

663
01:01:35,560 --> 01:01:37,835
The guy was some
big roller in suds.

664
01:01:41,440 --> 01:01:45,433
At least he was clean.
Some guys you wouldn't believe.

665
01:01:49,600 --> 01:01:51,670
The older ones,
they weren't so bad.

666
01:01:52,800 --> 01:01:54,950
Nice. Polite.

667
01:01:55,680 --> 01:01:57,318
Pulled you chair out for you.

668
01:02:00,040 --> 01:02:01,439
But the younger ones...

669
01:02:09,000 --> 01:02:11,150
It wasn't so bad.
I'd get a nice piece of steak,

670
01:02:11,320 --> 01:02:13,675
flowers, sometimes even a gift.

671
01:02:13,840 --> 01:02:15,592
Usually whatever the guy was into.

672
01:02:16,080 --> 01:02:18,230
I got a set of
socket wrenches once.

673
01:02:20,480 --> 01:02:24,109
Guy looked at me like
he'd given me 4 dozen roses.

674
01:02:29,640 --> 01:02:32,108
But I stayed at
the Hartford one time.

675
01:02:35,280 --> 01:02:39,114
You should see the rooms.
All satin and velvet.

676
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:41,114
And the bed...

677
01:02:41,280 --> 01:02:44,397
royal blue, trimmed in lace
clean as snow.

678
01:02:47,560 --> 01:02:50,597
Hard to believe a room like that
don't change your life.

679
01:02:52,480 --> 01:02:53,754
But it don't.

680
01:02:54,240 --> 01:02:56,071
The bed may be magic,

681
01:02:56,760 --> 01:02:58,193
but the mirror isn't.

682
01:02:59,600 --> 01:03:01,670
Still wake up the same old Susie.

683
01:03:06,240 --> 01:03:07,514
I didn't always.

684
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:09,274
You know, I mean...

685
01:03:10,480 --> 01:03:12,118
if I liked the guy.

686
01:03:16,880 --> 01:03:19,314
I never liked
the Hartford much myself.

687
01:03:31,760 --> 01:03:33,637
My neck, it's so tight.

688
01:03:34,440 --> 01:03:36,590
Usually singing relaxes me.

689
01:03:37,160 --> 01:03:38,912
But tonight...

690
01:03:45,840 --> 01:03:46,875
Thanks.

691
01:06:09,640 --> 01:06:12,154
You'd make a hell of a fireman,
you know that?

692
01:06:18,440 --> 01:06:21,034
Do you practice that at home
with a stopwatch?

693
01:06:24,080 --> 01:06:25,308
I didn't want to wake you.

694
01:06:27,280 --> 01:06:28,599
I'm an early riser.

695
01:06:35,840 --> 01:06:39,549
I didn't expect you to
buy be a corsage this morning.

696
01:06:42,680 --> 01:06:44,238
Your high school ring is safe.

697
01:07:06,680 --> 01:07:07,749
Shit!

698
01:07:12,120 --> 01:07:13,189
Shit!

699
01:07:49,280 --> 01:07:51,350
<i>That takes care of</i>
<i>the week of the 5th.</i>

700
01:07:51,840 --> 01:07:55,355
After that, we got the Avedon
or the Plaza, 4 day turn.

701
01:07:55,520 --> 01:07:56,839
What do you think, Jack?

702
01:07:58,760 --> 01:08:00,034
You with me, Jack?

703
01:08:00,960 --> 01:08:02,552
The Avedon's a dump.

704
01:08:03,200 --> 01:08:05,839
There's no cover, no minimum.
They water their drinks.

705
01:08:06,000 --> 01:08:07,718
Strictly the Fuller Brush crowd.

706
01:08:08,600 --> 01:08:11,956
It's not that bad. Besides,
Blacky Carson books the Avedon.

707
01:08:13,560 --> 01:08:15,152
He's always been good to us.

708
01:08:17,520 --> 01:08:20,637
- He hasn't been that good.
- Okay, we'll take the Plaza.

709
01:08:20,800 --> 01:08:23,758
- Then the Capri for 5 days.
- Not the Luau Lounge again.

710
01:08:23,960 --> 01:08:26,315
What the matter?
They don't salt their peanuts?

711
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:29,080
Singing "Feelings",
knee-deep in paper orchids

712
01:08:29,240 --> 01:08:31,071
and plastic Tiki lamps

713
01:08:31,240 --> 01:08:34,391
is not my idea
of a fun evening.

714
01:08:36,040 --> 01:08:38,679
Fun? Who promised you fun?
We get paid, remember?

715
01:08:38,840 --> 01:08:40,876
I'm saying,
maybe we should vote on it.

716
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:46,871
Maybe we should ask Jack
what he thinks.

717
01:08:47,040 --> 01:08:49,429
I don't have to.
I know what he thinks.

718
01:08:49,640 --> 01:08:52,074
It's 5 days, the money's green.
We're there.

719
01:08:54,800 --> 01:08:57,712
Speaking about "Feelings",
you might brush up on the lyrics.

720
01:08:57,880 --> 01:09:00,394
The other night,
you sang the first verse twice.

721
01:09:00,560 --> 01:09:01,675
Really?

722
01:09:02,600 --> 01:09:05,239
That explains the gasps
I heard from the audience.

723
01:09:06,040 --> 01:09:10,556
We trashed the Avedon, the Luau.
What's your beef with "Feelings"?

724
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:11,995
Nothing.

725
01:09:15,680 --> 01:09:17,079
Except, who cares?

726
01:09:17,400 --> 01:09:19,470
Does anybody really
need to hear "Feelings"

727
01:09:19,640 --> 01:09:21,039
again in a lifetime?

728
01:09:22,280 --> 01:09:23,793
It's like parsley.

729
01:09:23,960 --> 01:09:25,996
Take it away,
nobody knows the difference.

730
01:09:26,160 --> 01:09:27,878
"Feelings" isn't parsley.

731
01:09:28,080 --> 01:09:31,072
To you, "Feelings"
may be filet mignon.

732
01:09:31,440 --> 01:09:34,193
To me, it's parsley.
Less than parsley.

733
01:09:34,440 --> 01:09:37,113
Look, "Feelings",
despite what you think of it,

734
01:09:37,280 --> 01:09:39,669
is always a bright moment
and a crowd-pleaser.

735
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:42,957
Consequently, we have
an obligation to perform it.

736
01:09:43,440 --> 01:09:45,556
The audience would be disappointed.

737
01:09:45,880 --> 01:09:48,713
They weren't crying
on New Year's Eve.

738
01:09:54,440 --> 01:09:55,839
You passed over "Feelings"?

739
01:09:56,160 --> 01:09:57,229
Yeah.

740
01:09:58,520 --> 01:09:59,509
And...

741
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:01,955
"Bali Hai" went out
with the bath water, too.

742
01:10:06,320 --> 01:10:07,389
I see.

743
01:10:08,440 --> 01:10:11,716
The cat goes away and the mice
take over the orchestra.

744
01:10:11,880 --> 01:10:12,471
Hey,

745
01:10:12,880 --> 01:10:14,233
I ain't no mouse.

746
01:10:14,440 --> 01:10:15,998
That's right. You're parsley.

747
01:10:22,160 --> 01:10:25,277
This food's been sitting here
too long. It's making me sick.

748
01:10:35,400 --> 01:10:37,277
Why don't you loosen the leash?

749
01:10:38,320 --> 01:10:42,233
Let's not let a whiff of perfume
blow off 15 years. Be reasonable.

750
01:10:43,160 --> 01:10:46,835
I play 300 nights a year with you.
Is that reasonable enough?

751
01:12:19,920 --> 01:12:21,592
Can I have a double vodka, please?

752
01:13:16,960 --> 01:13:19,349
I was in the neighborhood.

753
01:13:31,400 --> 01:13:34,198
Listen, don't get nervous.
I just came by to...

754
01:13:37,360 --> 01:13:38,509
talk.

755
01:14:07,240 --> 01:14:09,151
I guess you found him, huh?

756
01:14:12,480 --> 01:14:13,469
Yeah.

757
01:14:16,560 --> 01:14:18,152
I came to walk Eddie.

758
01:14:18,760 --> 01:14:19,749
Come.

759
01:14:50,000 --> 01:14:51,479
Terry's Tap Room.

760
01:14:54,520 --> 01:14:56,351
First gig we ever played.

761
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:00,594
The owner gave us that bottle,
but wouldn't open it.

762
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:01,749
How come?

763
01:15:02,240 --> 01:15:04,071
Told us to save it.

764
01:15:07,280 --> 01:15:09,555
He said someday it would
soften the edges of the bad times.

765
01:15:09,720 --> 01:15:11,870
And make the good ones
seem even better.

766
01:15:14,760 --> 01:15:18,389
We should've drunk it before
we played Terry's Tap Room.

767
01:15:18,760 --> 01:15:20,079
Want some coffee?

768
01:15:27,640 --> 01:15:28,868
You want to leave?

769
01:15:30,640 --> 01:15:31,675
Listen.

770
01:15:34,080 --> 01:15:36,275
The reason I came last night is...

771
01:15:37,800 --> 01:15:40,439
I'm thinking about leaving.

772
01:15:41,400 --> 01:15:42,435
The act.

773
01:15:46,880 --> 01:15:49,678
I met this guy
at New Year's at the Hotel.

774
01:15:50,400 --> 01:15:52,630
And he liked my voice.

775
01:15:55,080 --> 01:15:58,197
He thinks I can sell
cat food just by singing about it.

776
01:16:00,320 --> 01:16:01,514
It's crazy, huh?

777
01:16:05,080 --> 01:16:06,195
Take it.

778
01:16:06,600 --> 01:16:09,990
I haven't decided yet.
I'm just thinking about it.

779
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:12,028
No, take it.

780
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:22,435
How long have you been
taking care of the kid upstairs?

781
01:16:23,480 --> 01:16:24,913
I don't take care of her.

782
01:16:25,920 --> 01:16:27,353
