01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:11,350
to snotty kids in the neighborhood.

1035
01:38:14,640 --> 01:38:16,039
Don't fool yourself.

1036
01:38:32,400 --> 01:38:33,435
Open it.

1037
01:38:36,720 --> 01:38:38,517
Open the fucking bottle.

1038
01:38:44,960 --> 01:38:46,632
Let's see what we got here.

1039
01:38:46,800 --> 01:38:48,756
We got the airport Ramada.

1040
01:38:51,120 --> 01:38:52,997
The Travel Lodge on 410.

1041
01:38:54,440 --> 01:38:55,873
And we got...

1042
01:38:58,400 --> 01:38:59,549
the Mallory.

1043
01:38:59,760 --> 01:39:01,239
I'll take the Mallory.

1044
01:39:01,400 --> 01:39:03,868
Forget it. I want the Mallory.
You take the Travel Lodge.

1045
01:39:31,640 --> 01:39:32,914
Not bad!

1046
01:39:39,600 --> 01:39:41,909
When was the last time
we played the Mallory?

1047
01:39:42,120 --> 01:39:43,838
'78, November.

1048
01:39:45,400 --> 01:39:48,676
It was someone's birthday.
Hallorin?

1049
01:39:49,760 --> 01:39:51,432
His daughter, sweet sixteen.

1050
01:39:52,040 --> 01:39:53,758
How could I forget?

1051
01:39:54,080 --> 01:39:55,559
What a nightmare.

1052
01:39:55,880 --> 01:39:57,199
She asked for it.

1053
01:39:57,360 --> 01:39:59,271
I told Howard we didn't
do vocals and he said:

1054
01:39:59,440 --> 01:40:01,078
"What my Sissie wants,

1055
01:40:01,640 --> 01:40:03,437
my Sissie gets".

1056
01:40:10,080 --> 01:40:11,399
She got it alright.

1057
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:14,077
You're risking your life.

1058
01:41:15,640 --> 01:41:16,789
You got a gun?

1059
01:41:17,520 --> 01:41:20,398
Car you're leaning on belongs to
a light heavyweight with attitude.

1060
01:41:22,000 --> 01:41:23,433
I'll take my chances.

1061
01:41:29,600 --> 01:41:30,669
You look good.

1062
01:41:31,680 --> 01:41:33,238
You look like shit.

1063
01:41:38,440 --> 01:41:40,032
No, I mean it. You look good.

1064
01:41:43,160 --> 01:41:45,310
I mean it, too.
You look like shit.

1065
01:41:48,040 --> 01:41:49,712
So how's the cat food business?

1066
01:41:52,440 --> 01:41:55,159
Terrific.
I'm doing vegetables now.

1067
01:41:57,280 --> 01:41:58,554
What kind?

1068
01:41:58,760 --> 01:41:59,749
Carrots,

1069
01:42:00,480 --> 01:42:01,674
peas.

1070
01:42:03,520 --> 01:42:05,158
None of the important ones.

1071
01:42:09,760 --> 01:42:11,079
You know...

1072
01:42:12,360 --> 01:42:13,475
the other night...

1073
01:42:14,440 --> 01:42:15,793
I was out of line.

1074
01:42:15,960 --> 01:42:17,439
No, I was out of line.

1075
01:42:24,280 --> 01:42:25,349
Well...

1076
01:42:26,600 --> 01:42:28,670
I was kind of rough on Egghead.

1077
01:42:31,360 --> 01:42:33,555
It beats the hell out of me,
but I kind of miss him.

1078
01:42:34,520 --> 01:42:35,669
Well...

1079
01:42:39,280 --> 01:42:42,272
he grows on you,
after a while.

1080
01:42:45,280 --> 01:42:46,998
So, did you find another girl?

1081
01:42:49,280 --> 01:42:50,508
I didn't look.

1082
01:42:57,960 --> 01:42:58,949
Well...

1083
01:42:59,360 --> 01:43:00,679
I'm going to be late.

1084
01:43:02,440 --> 01:43:05,398
<i>Peas, peas,</i>
<i>Try our peas.</i>

1085
01:43:05,560 --> 01:43:08,154
<i>Our peas are a delicacy.</i>

1086
01:43:10,600 --> 01:43:12,795
From "Strangers in the Night"
to that.

1087
01:43:13,240 --> 01:43:14,673
Funny world.

1088
01:43:20,960 --> 01:43:22,359
Well... bye, Baker.

1089
01:43:32,200 --> 01:43:33,553
Am I going to see you again?

1090
01:43:34,720 --> 01:43:35,914
What do you think?

1091
01:43:38,080 --> 01:43:39,069
Yeah,

1092
01:43:39,880 --> 01:43:41,871
I think I am going to see you again.

1093
01:43:47,320 --> 01:43:48,594
Intuition.

